data.chText: 轴（旋转物体假想的中心线）
data.enText: an imaginary line through the centre of an object, around which the object turns

data.chText: 火星自转一周的时间比地球长。
data.enText: Mars takes longer to revolve on its axis than the earth.

data.chText: （尤指图表中的）固定参考轴线，坐标轴
data.enText: a fixed line against which the positions of points are measured, especially points on a graph

data.chText: 对称中心线（将物体平分为二）
data.enText: a line that divides a shape into two equal parts

data.chText: 圆的对称中心线就是直径。
data.enText: The axis of a circle is its diameter.

data.chText: 轴心（国与国之间的协议或联盟）
data.enText: an agreement or alliance between two or more countries

means: 轴(旋转物体假想的中心线)
对称中心线(将物体平分为二)

tr: the center around which something rotates
serves as a pivot for turning the head
a straight line through a body or figure that satisfies certain conditions
a group of countries in special alliance
the main stem or central part about which plant organs or plant parts such as branches are arranged

value.def: An axis is an imaginary line through the middle of something.
An axis of a graph is one of the two lines on which the scales of measurement are marked.
